WEBVTT

00:03.655 --> 00:04.004
.

00:04.047 --> 00:05.353
- [gasps]

00:05.396 --> 00:06.789
Previously
on "The InBetween"...

00:06.832 --> 00:08.443
- Find me.
- I see ghosts.

00:08.486 --> 00:10.532
- ♪ Peter Rabbit

00:10.575 --> 00:13.100
♪ He'll be hopping along

00:13.143 --> 00:15.798
- The woman I saw was dead.
He'd taken out her eyes.

00:15.841 --> 00:17.234
- Perp's name was Ed Roven.

00:17.278 --> 00:18.670
Texas, mid '90s.

00:18.714 --> 00:21.369
Six women murdered.
Same MO, same signature.

00:21.412 --> 00:23.197
Roven made a mistake when
he left his last victim's son,

00:23.240 --> 00:24.633
Mark Waterman, alive.

00:24.676 --> 00:28.115
- I have PTSD from witnessing
Ed Roven kill my mother.

00:28.158 --> 00:29.333
- And that drove you to kill?

00:29.377 --> 00:31.074
It was very similar
to Ed Roven's work.

00:31.118 --> 00:32.249
- Roven's a ghost.

00:32.293 --> 00:33.859
When he talks to people,
they can't hear him.

00:33.903 --> 00:37.211
- It might be about time
we bust you out of here.

00:37.254 --> 00:39.735
- He told me to take your eyes.

00:39.778 --> 00:41.476
- [gasps]
- [grunts]

00:41.519 --> 00:43.086
- I went home.

00:43.130 --> 00:45.175
Baby Crystal was in the bath.

00:45.219 --> 00:47.177
And I just pushed.

00:47.221 --> 00:49.527
- I think she blames me
for what happened.

00:49.571 --> 00:51.486
- Oh, my mom's necklace.

00:51.529 --> 00:53.357
She never took this off.

00:53.401 --> 00:56.099
- Brian has what's called
a meningioma.

00:56.143 --> 00:59.537
It's a slow-growing
benign tumor on his brain.

00:59.581 --> 01:03.193
- Surgery's the only option?
- I need you to be okay.

01:03.237 --> 01:06.240
I can't have anything
happen to you.

01:07.241 --> 01:10.244
[indistinct chatter]

01:13.464 --> 01:16.424
[foreboding music]

01:16.467 --> 01:18.121
♪

01:18.165 --> 01:20.210
- Mom?

01:20.254 --> 01:22.560
♪

01:22.604 --> 01:24.388
Mom!

01:24.432 --> 01:26.782
♪

01:26.825 --> 01:29.741
Mom, stop!

01:29.785 --> 01:32.266
♪

01:32.309 --> 01:33.658
[door closes]

01:33.702 --> 01:35.921
♪

01:35.965 --> 01:38.228
Mom?

01:38.272 --> 01:41.797
♪

01:41.840 --> 01:44.408
Where are you going?

01:44.452 --> 01:47.498
♪

01:47.542 --> 01:49.152
[gasps]

01:49.196 --> 01:50.806
Roven, what are you
doing here?

01:50.849 --> 01:54.244
- Hey, there, Cottontail.

01:54.288 --> 01:56.855
Looking for someone?

01:56.899 --> 01:59.467
- Where is she?
- See for yourself.

01:59.510 --> 02:02.644
♪

02:02.687 --> 02:03.645
- Mom?

02:03.688 --> 02:05.777
- Cassie.

02:05.821 --> 02:08.780
[ominous music]

02:08.824 --> 02:15.831
♪

02:17.267 --> 02:19.617
I'm over here.

02:19.661 --> 02:21.184
- You're a witch!
- [screams]

02:21.228 --> 02:23.708
[gasps, panting]

02:23.752 --> 02:27.538
[whimpering]

02:29.236 --> 02:30.715
- Let's go over it
one more time.

02:30.759 --> 02:33.196
Um, my social security card
is right here.

02:33.240 --> 02:34.719
My most recent will...

02:34.763 --> 02:38.941
and, uh, my advanced directive,
which explicitly lays out

02:38.984 --> 02:40.899
all of my wishes
should the worst happen.

02:40.943 --> 02:42.988
- Babe, we've been over this.

02:43.032 --> 02:45.295
You're going to be fine.

02:45.339 --> 02:47.732
- We ran through all
the worst-case scenarios,

02:47.776 --> 02:50.474
which aren't going to happen--
knock wood.

02:50.518 --> 02:51.823
[knocks on table]
We each have a copy

02:51.867 --> 02:53.129
of the prime directive--

02:53.173 --> 02:55.610
- Advanced directive.
- Which we won't need.

02:55.653 --> 02:58.308
- The surgery is tomorrow.
- Look, we're all nervous.

02:58.352 --> 03:00.354
But you're going
to a great hospital,

03:00.397 --> 03:01.790
and you've got one
of the best brain surgeons

03:01.833 --> 03:04.749
in the world flying in.

03:04.793 --> 03:06.447
- There is a snowstorm coming.

03:06.490 --> 03:07.883
I hope that doesn't delay
her flight.

03:07.926 --> 03:09.972
Knock on wood.
[knocks on table]

03:10.015 --> 03:11.669
- Are you gonna be all right
waiting at the hospital

03:11.713 --> 03:13.323
during the procedure?

03:13.367 --> 03:16.370
I know how upsetting
that energy is for you.

03:16.413 --> 03:18.023
- I've been going over
every day--

03:18.067 --> 03:20.374
walking around, kind of
inoculating myself to it.

03:20.417 --> 03:21.549
By the time you go in,

03:21.592 --> 03:23.594
I should be able
to block most of it out.

03:23.638 --> 03:26.554
I did want to wear
my lucky sweater, though.

03:26.597 --> 03:28.120
They gray one.
Is that here?

03:28.164 --> 03:30.819
- Washed, folded, and ready
to work its magic on my behalf.

03:30.862 --> 03:32.386
It's in the dresser
in your room.

03:32.429 --> 03:33.822
- Thank you.

03:33.865 --> 03:36.781
Knock more wood while I'm gone,
just to be safe.

03:38.305 --> 03:41.308
- It's okay.
It's all right.

03:41.351 --> 03:42.657
It's gonna be
all right, babe.

03:42.700 --> 03:46.269
It's gonna be all right.
- [sighs]

03:51.448 --> 03:53.015
[sinister music]

03:53.058 --> 03:55.452
- [gasps,
whimpering]

03:55.496 --> 03:58.455
[panting]

03:58.499 --> 04:00.718
♪

04:00.762 --> 04:02.894
- The guy you described
sounds like Mark Waterman,

04:02.938 --> 04:04.418
but according
to this county jail video,

04:04.461 --> 04:05.549
there he is in his cell.

04:05.593 --> 04:07.029
He couldn't have
killed anyone.

04:07.072 --> 04:08.726
- Yeah, that's the guy I saw.

04:08.770 --> 04:12.295
[cell phone vibrating]

04:12.339 --> 04:13.470
- Is that work?

04:13.514 --> 04:16.081
[suspenseful music]

04:16.125 --> 04:18.910
- A woman's been murdered.

04:18.954 --> 04:21.739
Her throat was cut.

04:21.783 --> 04:26.309
♪

04:26.353 --> 04:27.745
[indistinct chatter]

04:27.789 --> 04:29.443
[sighs]
What have we got?

04:29.486 --> 04:32.097
- Well, the victim's name
is Suzy Lim, 32.

04:32.141 --> 04:33.534
A schoolteacher.

04:33.577 --> 04:35.579
- Looks like he caught her
by surprise.

04:35.623 --> 04:37.538
No defensive wounds
on her hands,

04:37.581 --> 04:39.322
just a clean, straight cut
from left to right on the neck.

04:39.366 --> 04:40.541
- Robbery?

04:40.584 --> 04:42.586
- Television, computer,
cell phone--

04:42.630 --> 04:44.109
they were all left out
in the open.

04:44.153 --> 04:46.503
No jewelry was missing,
but her wallet was gone.

04:46.547 --> 04:47.504
- Who found her?

04:47.548 --> 04:48.679
- Neighbor called 911

04:48.723 --> 04:50.159
when she saw
an unidentified male

04:50.202 --> 04:52.553
exiting through the victim's
kitchen door in a big hurry.

04:52.596 --> 04:53.815
- Did she get a description?

04:53.858 --> 04:55.643
- Caucasian, bearded,
about 6 feet tall--

04:55.686 --> 04:56.992
blue pants
and a yellow parka.

04:57.035 --> 04:59.081
- Just got a call
from Suzy Lim's credit union.

04:59.124 --> 05:00.952
Her ATM card was used
at a cash machine

05:00.996 --> 05:01.997
just about two blocks
from here.

05:02.040 --> 05:03.694
- Did you send unis over?
- Yeah.

05:03.738 --> 05:05.783
The guy's gone, but the owner's
pulling up the security tape.

05:05.827 --> 05:11.702
♪

05:11.746 --> 05:14.401
- I know this guy.

05:14.444 --> 05:16.881
His name is Calvin Hayes.
We need to bring him in.

05:16.925 --> 05:18.448
Alert all precincts
in the city.

05:18.492 --> 05:20.058
- On it.

05:20.102 --> 05:21.625
- How do you know Hayes?

05:21.669 --> 05:23.018
- He's the man
that attacked Cassie

05:23.061 --> 05:24.672
in front of Council last month.

05:24.715 --> 05:27.022
She had a dream about him
last night.

05:28.676 --> 05:31.679
- [low growl]
- [scoffs]

05:31.722 --> 05:34.029
I don't have time
for you, Ed.

05:34.072 --> 05:36.553
- Won't be a minute.

05:36.597 --> 05:38.990
Just wanted to say
a proper good-bye is all.

05:39.034 --> 05:40.818
- Are you finally
going somewhere?

05:40.862 --> 05:42.472
- Oh, no.

05:42.516 --> 05:44.605
Not me.

05:44.648 --> 05:46.998
But give my best
to you and yours.

05:47.042 --> 05:50.045
[dark music]

05:50.088 --> 05:53.091
♪

05:53.135 --> 05:55.529
- If Hayes was arrested
for aggravated assault,

05:55.572 --> 05:56.834
what's he doing
out of jail already?

05:56.878 --> 05:58.967
- He was released O.R.
due to overcrowding.

05:59.010 --> 06:00.490
- Oh, you're kidding me.

06:00.534 --> 06:01.970
- We've got every unit
in the city on the street

06:02.013 --> 06:02.971
looking for him.

06:03.014 --> 06:04.233
We will get him back
in custody.

06:04.276 --> 06:05.843
- Well, I doubt that's gonna
bring much comfort

06:05.887 --> 06:07.149
to Suzy Lim's family.

06:07.192 --> 06:09.064
♪

06:09.107 --> 06:10.587
- Maria.

06:10.631 --> 06:12.546
You're checking into Suzy Lim's
friends and family, yes?

06:12.589 --> 06:14.156
- Yeah.

06:14.199 --> 06:16.071
- See if she has any connection
to anyone at county jail,

06:16.114 --> 06:18.116
and if so, find out if she
has ever crossed paths

06:18.160 --> 06:19.770
with Mark Waterman.

06:19.814 --> 06:21.859
- On it.

06:21.903 --> 06:24.558
- Unis picked up Hayes
at a homeless camp on Burnage.

06:24.601 --> 06:26.081
They're bringing him in now.

06:26.124 --> 06:28.039
♪

06:28.083 --> 06:29.693
- Hey.

06:29.737 --> 06:31.956
How's the crowd been so far?
- Good.

06:32.000 --> 06:34.045
But we're running out of
the cinnamon-infused bourbon,

06:34.089 --> 06:36.831
so don't push
the spicy Manhattans.

06:36.874 --> 06:39.442
- Well, we need to unload some
of that vanilla gin anyways.

06:39.486 --> 06:41.531
- Ugh. Good luck with that.
I'm out of here.

06:41.575 --> 06:43.881
Bye.

06:43.925 --> 06:46.406
[sniffs]

06:47.581 --> 06:50.671
[sinister music]

06:50.714 --> 06:57.721
♪

06:59.244 --> 07:02.030
[bones crack]
[gasps]

07:02.073 --> 07:05.947
♪

07:05.990 --> 07:08.558
- Hey, there, Cottontail.

07:08.602 --> 07:10.560
♪

07:10.604 --> 07:13.563
[indistinct chatter]

07:13.607 --> 07:16.523
[mellow music playing
over speakers]

07:17.872 --> 07:19.917
- I don't know why
you brought me in here.

07:19.961 --> 07:22.659
I was just minding
my own business.

07:22.703 --> 07:24.052
- Minding your own business?

07:24.095 --> 07:25.793
As in attacking young women
with sharp objects.

07:25.836 --> 07:28.839
- [scoffs]
You got the wrong guy.

07:30.754 --> 07:33.627
- You recognize her?

07:33.670 --> 07:36.020
You had her ATM card.

07:36.064 --> 07:37.544
- I found it.

07:37.587 --> 07:39.633
- Your fingerprints were on
her kitchen door, Calvin.

07:39.676 --> 07:42.157
When unis picked you up, you
had her blood on your clothes.

07:42.200 --> 07:43.593
- We know you killed her.

07:43.637 --> 07:45.160
What we want to know is why.

07:45.203 --> 07:47.641
♪

07:47.684 --> 07:49.294
[indistinct voices]

07:49.338 --> 07:53.037
- I'm just an instrument
of the Witch Hunter.

07:53.081 --> 07:56.693
Change is brought
to the Earth through me,

07:56.737 --> 07:59.261
but I'm not worthy enough
to know why.

07:59.304 --> 08:01.872
[tense music]

08:01.916 --> 08:04.614
- Who's the Witch Hunter?
- It's not a person.

08:04.658 --> 08:06.181
He's like a...

08:06.224 --> 08:08.531
[softly]
Spirit guide.

08:08.575 --> 08:11.795
- How does this spirit guide
communicate with you?

08:11.839 --> 08:15.059
- He talks to me...
[laughs]

08:15.103 --> 08:16.887
Tells me
what I need to know,

08:16.931 --> 08:19.629
which road to take.

08:19.673 --> 08:21.979
- What did he tell you
about Suzy Lim?

08:22.023 --> 08:24.678
- He said
she was sticking her nose

08:24.721 --> 08:26.027
where it didn't belong.

08:26.070 --> 08:28.072
Said she was a snitch.

08:28.116 --> 08:30.597
Said she had to die.

08:30.640 --> 08:32.816
- [breathes deeply]

08:32.860 --> 08:35.689
♪

08:35.732 --> 08:38.648
Snitching about what?
- He didn't say.

08:38.692 --> 08:40.084
- Last month you were arrested

08:40.128 --> 08:41.999
for attacking
another young woman.

08:42.043 --> 08:43.610
- Uh-huh.

08:43.653 --> 08:47.657
He told me she was hurting
people with her eyes.

08:47.701 --> 08:50.094
They needed plucked.
[laughs]

08:50.138 --> 08:51.922
Bitch hit me
with the pepper spray

08:51.966 --> 08:53.837
before I got a chance,
but next time--

08:53.881 --> 08:55.273
- There's no next time, Calvin.

08:55.317 --> 08:56.579
You are spending the rest
of your life in prison.

08:56.623 --> 08:59.364
- Tom.

08:59.408 --> 09:02.193
♪

09:02.237 --> 09:06.067
- ♪ Peter Rabbit
and the little red hen ♪

09:06.110 --> 09:10.854
♪ Talking things over
in the high-wired pen ♪

09:10.898 --> 09:14.728
♪ Along came McDonald
with his trusty gun ♪

09:14.771 --> 09:17.382
♪ And he goes

09:17.426 --> 09:19.341
♪ "Everybody run"

09:19.384 --> 09:21.038
♪

09:21.082 --> 09:23.171
♪ Peter Rabbit

09:23.214 --> 09:26.348
♪ He'll be hopping along

09:26.391 --> 09:29.351
[dramatic music]

09:29.394 --> 09:33.921
♪

09:37.881 --> 09:40.797
County says Waterman is still
safely locked in his cell,

09:40.841 --> 09:42.407
but they'll double up security.

09:42.451 --> 09:44.366
- Then I don't know
why I keep seeing him.

09:44.409 --> 09:46.324
- I think I do.

09:46.368 --> 09:48.500
When's the last time you spoke
with Ed Roven?

09:48.544 --> 09:49.850
- Today.

09:49.893 --> 09:52.243
He's still pissed we found
Millie Pierce's body.

09:52.287 --> 09:54.376
- Yeah, I don't want
to humanize a vicious killer,

09:54.419 --> 09:56.552
but Roven was sentimental
about Millie.

09:56.596 --> 09:57.640
- Yeah.

09:57.684 --> 09:59.424
- He wanted to keep her
for himself.

09:59.468 --> 10:02.863
- Did he threaten you?
- Well, not in so many words.

10:02.906 --> 10:03.864
Why?

10:03.907 --> 10:05.561
- Calvin Hayes--
the homeless guy

10:05.605 --> 10:06.823
that attacked you last month--

10:06.867 --> 10:08.651
he murdered a woman
this morning.

10:08.695 --> 10:10.174
He cut her throat.

10:10.218 --> 10:11.654
- You think Roven told him
to do it?

10:11.698 --> 10:14.439
- I don't know. I'm still
putting the pieces together.

10:14.483 --> 10:18.443
But listen--I think that Hayes
can hear Roven...

10:18.487 --> 10:22.447
and I think Waterman
can hear Roven.

10:22.491 --> 10:24.145
Think about it.

10:24.188 --> 10:26.495
If someone is just
a little bit perceptive

10:26.538 --> 10:28.366
and Roven is persistent,

10:28.410 --> 10:31.326
couldn't he start to sound
like a voice in your head?

10:31.369 --> 10:33.633
- And if you already have
violent tendencies,

10:33.676 --> 10:35.635
maybe he can get you
to kill.

10:35.678 --> 10:38.681
- So you think
that Roven and Waterman...

10:38.725 --> 10:40.509
they're planning
something now?

10:40.552 --> 10:42.250
- I'm not sure yet.

10:42.293 --> 10:44.818
But the woman that you just saw
Waterman murder at the bar,

10:44.861 --> 10:46.689
can you describe her
to our sketch artist?

10:46.733 --> 10:49.823
Maybe the FBI can identify her.
- Yeah, I can do that.

10:49.866 --> 10:52.652
But I need something
from you.

10:52.695 --> 10:55.176
There's an FBI file
on Roven, right?

10:55.219 --> 10:57.395
- Yeah, field office sent it
over during the Waterman case.

10:57.439 --> 10:59.223
- Can I take a look at it?

10:59.267 --> 11:00.616
- Why?

11:00.660 --> 11:02.400
- Because I need to know
everything about Roven...

11:02.444 --> 11:04.272
the stuff
you can't find online,

11:04.315 --> 11:05.621
that dark stuff.

11:05.665 --> 11:07.362
- To what end?

11:07.405 --> 11:09.320
- There are places far worse
than the inbetween.

11:09.364 --> 11:10.757
It's time that Ed Roven
went there,

11:10.800 --> 11:13.455
and I think that that...

11:13.498 --> 11:15.805
that could solve
all our problems.

11:15.849 --> 11:18.590
- If it's all right with
Asante, it's all right with me.

11:18.634 --> 11:21.811
- I'll grab the drive.

11:21.855 --> 11:23.595
- And listen, you,

11:23.639 --> 11:25.728
I am putting a car
on your house

11:25.772 --> 11:26.947
until this is all over.

11:26.990 --> 11:28.818
You understand?
- Yeah.

11:28.862 --> 11:30.472
Totally okay with that.

11:30.515 --> 11:32.866
- And if you need anything
else, you let me know, okay?

11:32.909 --> 11:35.216
- Thanks.
- Please.

11:35.259 --> 11:37.479
- Why don't I walk you upstairs
to Forensics,

11:37.522 --> 11:39.220
make sure they send the sketch
to the FBI?

11:39.263 --> 11:41.788
- Great, thanks.

11:41.831 --> 11:43.224
- Hey, Tom.
- Yeah?

11:43.267 --> 11:45.530
- All right, I found Suzy Lim's
connection to county.

11:45.574 --> 11:48.664
It's her. She volunteers
at the jail once a month--

11:48.708 --> 11:49.839
tutors prisoners.

11:49.883 --> 11:51.623
See that name?

11:51.667 --> 11:53.930
- Mark Waterman
was one of her students.

11:53.974 --> 11:56.977
[indistinct chatter]

12:02.373 --> 12:04.288
- Brian?

12:04.332 --> 12:06.508
What are you doing here?

12:06.551 --> 12:09.511
[ominous music]

12:09.554 --> 12:14.472
♪

12:14.516 --> 12:15.909
- Forensics sent this
down for you.

12:15.952 --> 12:18.041
Said they emailed Asante's
friend at the Bureau, too.

12:18.085 --> 12:20.783
- Thank you.

12:20.827 --> 12:22.785
♪

12:22.829 --> 12:25.962
- Tom, I just hung up
with the warden at county.

12:26.006 --> 12:28.791
He said that you requested they
put Mark Waterman in solitary.

12:28.835 --> 12:30.401
- That's right.
We think he may be connected

12:30.445 --> 12:31.489
to Suzy Lim's murder.

12:31.533 --> 12:33.013
- Yeah, the warden
thinks so, too.

12:33.056 --> 12:35.406
He just learned
that Suzy Lim requested

12:35.450 --> 12:37.017
a meeting with him
this morning.

12:37.060 --> 12:40.368
She told his assistant
it was about Mark Waterman.

12:40.411 --> 12:41.586
- Did she say anything else?

12:41.630 --> 12:43.414
- Just that it was
an urgent matter.

12:43.458 --> 12:45.373
An hour later,
she was murdered.

12:45.416 --> 12:47.070
Waterman is in solitary now,

12:47.114 --> 12:48.768
and they're gonna search
his cell.

12:48.811 --> 12:51.509
If he was planning something,
they'll put a stop to it quick.

12:51.553 --> 12:53.555
Good work.

12:53.598 --> 12:55.862
♪

12:55.905 --> 12:58.821
[indistinct chatter]

12:58.865 --> 13:00.431
- Hey.

13:00.475 --> 13:02.433
- Hey.

13:02.477 --> 13:04.305
Y-you didn't tell Tom
you were meeting me?

13:04.348 --> 13:07.003
- I told him I was coming here
to grab dinner.

13:07.047 --> 13:09.310
What's going on?
- I have a problem.

13:09.353 --> 13:11.051
Uh...

13:11.094 --> 13:14.532
right now you're
the only person I can talk to.

13:14.576 --> 13:17.884
The day that Sally
passed away...

13:17.927 --> 13:20.060
remember I said
I had seen her?

13:20.103 --> 13:21.713
I saw the two
of you together.

13:21.757 --> 13:23.411
- I remember.
Sure.

13:23.454 --> 13:27.545
- That wasn't the first time
I had seen her.

13:27.589 --> 13:31.071
Earlier, I saw her fetch.

13:31.114 --> 13:32.550
It's like a premonition.

13:32.594 --> 13:34.117
You see a person's spirit,
but they're still alive,

13:34.161 --> 13:37.817
but usually it means
they're gonna die.

13:37.860 --> 13:39.731
I just saw Brian.

13:39.775 --> 13:42.082
[somber music]

13:42.125 --> 13:44.824
I don't know what to do.

13:44.867 --> 13:46.956
Should I tell him?
Should I tell Tom?

13:47.000 --> 13:49.611
- You said it "usually"
means death.

13:49.654 --> 13:52.919
- Nothing's ever
a certainty, I guess.

13:52.962 --> 13:55.878
- So what if Brian
postponed his procedure?

13:55.922 --> 13:58.054
- I'm not sure
that would take care of it.

13:58.098 --> 13:59.926
Or worse,
maybe making that change

13:59.969 --> 14:03.494
is what brings about
the bad outcome.

14:03.538 --> 14:04.931
- [sighs]

14:04.974 --> 14:07.498
- Do you wish I had told you
about Sally?

14:07.542 --> 14:08.891
♪

14:08.935 --> 14:11.024
Would it have changed
anything?

14:11.067 --> 14:14.114
♪

14:14.157 --> 14:16.681
- No, it wouldn't.

14:16.725 --> 14:18.118
♪

14:18.161 --> 14:20.860
- So you're saying I should--
I should just leave it.

14:20.903 --> 14:22.731
- If telling them
won't solve the problem--

14:22.774 --> 14:24.385
you know, if we can't know

14:24.428 --> 14:26.387
which decision's
the right one...

14:26.430 --> 14:27.910
♪

14:27.954 --> 14:31.609
I guess that's
what I'm saying, yeah.

14:31.653 --> 14:32.784
Hey.

14:32.828 --> 14:36.005
I'm so sorry
you're dealing with this.

14:36.049 --> 14:37.180
- Thanks.

14:37.224 --> 14:39.400
[cell phone vibrating]

14:39.443 --> 14:41.010
♪

14:41.054 --> 14:43.491
You got to go.
I'll be okay.

14:43.534 --> 14:45.885
- All right.
I'll call you later.

14:45.928 --> 14:51.412
♪

14:53.153 --> 14:54.719
What happened?

14:54.763 --> 14:56.547
- Waterman was in solitary
when he began showing symptoms

14:56.591 --> 14:57.679
of a heart attack.

14:57.722 --> 14:58.854
- [sighs]
He's got to be faking it.

14:58.898 --> 15:00.551
- His blood pressure
was off the charts.

15:00.595 --> 15:02.205
They're rushing him
to the nearest facility

15:02.249 --> 15:03.511
with a cardiac unit--

15:03.554 --> 15:05.034
Woodgate Memorial.
- [sighs]

15:05.078 --> 15:06.949
That's where Waterman worked
as an EMT.

15:06.993 --> 15:08.646
He knows that place
inside and out.

15:08.690 --> 15:09.996
- That was the plan all along.

15:10.039 --> 15:12.650
He's gonna try and escape
from that hospital.

15:15.044 --> 15:15.262
.

15:15.305 --> 15:18.221
[indistinct chatter]

15:18.265 --> 15:20.397
- What happened?
- We got your call.

15:20.441 --> 15:21.703
We came up
to check on the prisoner.

15:21.746 --> 15:23.357
He'd already made his move.

15:23.400 --> 15:25.446
- Looks like he lured the guard
into his room, disabled him,

15:25.489 --> 15:27.404
and then escaped
down a back staircase.

15:27.448 --> 15:28.971
- Establish
a five-block perimeter.

15:29.015 --> 15:30.581
Start a house-to-house search.

15:30.625 --> 15:32.453
He could not have gotten far
without someone spotting him.

15:32.496 --> 15:34.063
- Yes, sir.

15:34.107 --> 15:36.500
- [sighs] We put out a BOLO
and alerted the news stations.

15:36.544 --> 15:38.720
They're blasting Waterman's
picture all over town.

15:38.763 --> 15:41.114
- I'm looking over the footage
for the last hour.

15:41.157 --> 15:43.246
That stairway he went down
leads to the basement.

15:43.290 --> 15:44.465
Connects the entire complex.

15:44.508 --> 15:45.988
There are eight exits
he could have used

15:46.032 --> 15:47.598
without tripping an alarm.

15:47.642 --> 15:49.122
Hold on.
What's that right there?

15:49.165 --> 15:50.775
That's him.
He's had someone pick him up.

15:50.819 --> 15:52.560
It's a woman.

15:52.603 --> 15:54.605
- No plates.
- Run the make and model.

15:54.649 --> 15:56.999
- Yeah, just send it
to my phone.

15:57.043 --> 15:59.262
And thanks, man.
I owe you.

15:59.306 --> 16:01.134
That sketch Cassie did

16:01.177 --> 16:02.657
of the woman she saw
with Waterman--

16:02.700 --> 16:04.485
my buddy from the FBI
just ID'd her.

16:04.528 --> 16:06.269
- Who is she?

16:06.313 --> 16:09.490
- Her name's Deborah Strong--
552 Bloomfield Road,

16:09.533 --> 16:11.013
and she drives
a white four-door,

16:11.057 --> 16:12.580
just like the one
that picked up Waterman.

16:12.623 --> 16:13.929
- She's Waterman's accomplice.

16:13.973 --> 16:15.713
- But when Cassie saw
Deborah being murdered,

16:15.757 --> 16:18.107
she was actually alive and well
helping Waterman escape.

16:18.151 --> 16:20.240
- Cassie wasn't seeing
the past.

16:20.283 --> 16:22.242
She was seeing the future.

16:22.285 --> 16:24.505
- So maybe we're not too late.

16:27.203 --> 16:30.163
[ominous music]

16:30.206 --> 16:37.213
♪

16:48.398 --> 16:49.617
- [sighs]

16:49.660 --> 16:51.358
[knocking on door]

16:53.142 --> 16:55.231
- Cassie!
- Hannah.

16:55.275 --> 16:56.798
I hope it's all right
I came by without calling.

16:56.841 --> 16:58.626
- Of course. Come in.

16:58.669 --> 17:02.151
Come by anytime.
You're always welcome.

17:02.195 --> 17:04.153
- How have you been?

17:04.197 --> 17:06.764
- I've been okay, thanks.

17:06.808 --> 17:09.680
Some bad days, but mostly good.

17:09.724 --> 17:11.726
I still miss Abigail so much.

17:11.769 --> 17:14.381
But I talk to her now,

17:14.424 --> 17:17.079
and that seems
to make things easier.

17:17.123 --> 17:18.385
- Mm.

17:18.428 --> 17:20.387
- Sometimes I wake up
in the middle of the night,

17:20.430 --> 17:23.825
and I hear Crystal laughing
in her room,

17:23.868 --> 17:27.089
talking to someone,
playing peekaboo.

17:27.133 --> 17:29.396
I like to think it's Abigail...

17:29.439 --> 17:30.658
come for a visit.

17:30.701 --> 17:33.182
- Babies
can often see spirits.

17:33.226 --> 17:36.272
They just--they usually
grow out of it.

17:36.316 --> 17:37.752
- [sighs]

17:37.795 --> 17:40.363
I hope she can always see
her sister...

17:40.407 --> 17:42.757
or at least feel her near.

17:42.800 --> 17:46.500
- The truth is, Hannah,
I'm looking for Abigail.

17:46.543 --> 17:48.371
It's important,
and I was hoping

17:48.415 --> 17:49.894
that she would be here
with you.

17:49.938 --> 17:52.288
If you think
that she visits the baby,

17:52.332 --> 17:55.596
would it be okay if maybe
I sat in Crystal's room...

17:55.639 --> 17:56.771
for a minute?

17:56.814 --> 17:58.555
- Of course.

17:58.599 --> 18:00.340
It's just up the stairs.

18:00.383 --> 18:01.689
- Thank you.

18:01.732 --> 18:04.561
[distant sirens wailing]

18:04.605 --> 18:05.867
[indistinct chatter]

18:05.910 --> 18:08.217
- What's the story?
- Spoke with the landlord.

18:08.261 --> 18:09.740
He says Deborah's car
isn't in the lot.

18:09.784 --> 18:11.264
It looks like she hasn't been
home all night.

18:11.307 --> 18:12.917
- She and Waterman
are holed up somewhere else.

18:12.961 --> 18:15.137
Anyone in the apartment now?
- Yeah, just her mom, Lorraine.

18:15.181 --> 18:16.878
Deborah lives with her.
- All right.

18:16.921 --> 18:18.923
- I don't understand
any of this.

18:18.967 --> 18:20.664
What do you want with Deborah?

18:20.708 --> 18:22.231
- We need to talk to her
about a friend of hers.

18:22.275 --> 18:23.841
- Did she ever mention
the name Mark?

18:23.885 --> 18:26.757
- The boyfriend.
Debbie's crazy about him.

18:26.801 --> 18:28.455
But she never
brings him around.

18:28.498 --> 18:31.240
She's always going to see him.

18:31.284 --> 18:33.329
- How long since
your daughter's been home?

18:33.373 --> 18:35.418
- She left last night
and hasn't been back.

18:35.462 --> 18:36.941
I had to get my own breakfast.

18:36.985 --> 18:40.641
I had to remember
to take my pills.

18:40.684 --> 18:42.947
- What medications
do you take, Mrs. Strong?

18:42.991 --> 18:44.471
- Everything under the sun.

18:44.514 --> 18:46.777
Pills for pain,
pills for my cholesterol,

18:46.821 --> 18:49.519
pills to help me sleep,
pills to wake me up.

18:49.563 --> 18:50.955
- Baltoxin?

18:50.999 --> 18:52.957
- Well, that one
keeps my heart beating.

18:53.001 --> 18:54.872
[tense music]

18:54.916 --> 18:57.266
- Excuse us one second.

18:57.310 --> 18:59.181
♪

18:59.225 --> 19:00.748
Are you thinking
what I'm thinking?

19:00.791 --> 19:02.576
- Maybe Deborah smuggled in
a few of those pills

19:02.619 --> 19:03.881
into jail
on one of her visits.

19:03.925 --> 19:05.492
- And Waterman takes the pills,

19:05.535 --> 19:07.407
makes his healthy heart
start to race.

19:07.450 --> 19:08.886
Looks like he's having
a heart attack.

19:08.930 --> 19:09.931
- Yeah.

19:09.974 --> 19:11.498
- Suzy Lim
was tutoring Waterman.

19:11.541 --> 19:13.282
If he and Deborah
were planning an escape,

19:13.326 --> 19:14.631
maybe she got onto it.

19:14.675 --> 19:16.416
Calvin Hayes said
she was a snitch, remember?

19:16.459 --> 19:18.853
- Then Ed Roven gets Hayes
to murder her

19:18.896 --> 19:20.202
before she can tell
the warden.

19:20.246 --> 19:22.335
- Exactly.
- Think I found something.

19:22.378 --> 19:24.511
Two weeks ago, Deborah rented
a furnished apartment

19:24.554 --> 19:26.556
in a building on Barber Street.

19:26.600 --> 19:28.384
- Mrs. Strong?

19:28.428 --> 19:30.256
Was Deborah planning
to move out?

19:30.299 --> 19:32.475
- Of course not.
Who would take care of me?

19:32.519 --> 19:33.781
- According
to the building manager,

19:33.824 --> 19:35.565
Deborah only picked up
the key yesterday.

19:35.609 --> 19:36.914
- That must be
where they're hiding out.

19:36.958 --> 19:38.655
- Let's get the marshals
over there.

19:38.699 --> 19:40.483
[sirens wailing]

19:40.527 --> 19:43.356
[suspenseful music]

19:43.399 --> 19:50.406
♪

19:56.673 --> 19:58.719
- Seattle PD!

19:58.762 --> 20:01.548
[door thuds open]

20:01.591 --> 20:03.506
Two bedrooms--search!

20:03.550 --> 20:05.247
- Clear.
- Clear.

20:05.291 --> 20:06.335
- Clear.
- Clear.

20:06.379 --> 20:08.337
- Get an EMT here, now.

20:08.381 --> 20:10.905
Deborah.
- [gasps]

20:10.948 --> 20:12.689
- It's all right.
- Help me.

20:12.733 --> 20:13.690
- It's all right.

20:13.734 --> 20:16.258
Listen, where is Waterman?

20:16.302 --> 20:19.348
- I don't know.
He--he attacked me.

20:19.392 --> 20:22.003
I thought he was gonna kill me,
but then he stopped.

20:22.046 --> 20:23.700
He stopped.

20:23.744 --> 20:25.920
He said "police," and...

20:25.963 --> 20:27.791
[voice breaking]
And then he ran out.

20:27.835 --> 20:29.837
- We just missed him. Check
the emergency stairs, now.

20:29.880 --> 20:30.838
- Yes, sir.
Let's go.

20:30.881 --> 20:32.753
- He knew we were coming.
How?

20:32.796 --> 20:35.973
- Mark's special like that.

20:36.017 --> 20:37.714
He knows things.

20:37.758 --> 20:42.719
♪

20:42.763 --> 20:45.983
- Roven told him.
[sirens approaching]

20:49.291 --> 20:49.465
.

20:49.509 --> 20:52.120
[childlike music]

20:52.163 --> 20:56.820
♪

20:56.864 --> 20:59.301
- [sighs contentedly]

20:59.345 --> 21:01.477
♪

21:01.521 --> 21:04.001
[softly]
Hi.

21:04.045 --> 21:05.960
Hi.

21:06.003 --> 21:08.310
[eerie whooshing]

21:08.354 --> 21:11.139
- She's sweet, isn't she?

21:11.182 --> 21:13.968
I can't believe
I ever wanted to hurt her.

21:14.011 --> 21:17.145
- You weren't thinking straight
at the time.

21:17.188 --> 21:20.104
- I guess not.

21:20.148 --> 21:23.456
Thank you for stopping me
and for helping me get unstuck.

21:23.499 --> 21:26.285
I can go all sorts
of places now.

21:26.328 --> 21:28.156
- Did you ever find
your Aunt Molly?

21:28.199 --> 21:29.592
- Not yet.

21:29.636 --> 21:32.465
- Because I'm looking
for someone.

21:32.508 --> 21:36.164
She's unstuck, too, and I don't
know how to find her.

21:36.207 --> 21:39.254
I was hoping maybe you could.

21:39.298 --> 21:42.301
- The last vocabulary word
I learned before I died

21:42.344 --> 21:43.432
was "vast"--

21:43.476 --> 21:46.479
a very great extent
or quantity.

21:46.522 --> 21:49.482
The inbetween is vast...

21:49.525 --> 21:51.310
but I can try.

21:51.353 --> 21:53.486
- Her name is Millie.

21:53.529 --> 21:56.402
Can I show you a photo?

21:57.925 --> 22:00.101
[car beeps]
[shivers]

22:02.190 --> 22:03.452
[window whirring]

22:03.496 --> 22:05.889
Hey.
Crazy weather, huh?

22:05.933 --> 22:07.413
- I know, I can't believe it.

22:07.456 --> 22:10.241
But I hear
it's gonna stop soon.

22:10.285 --> 22:13.897
[indistinct chatter
over police radio]

22:13.941 --> 22:15.464
[eerie whooshing]

22:15.508 --> 22:17.945
- You need to get home now.

22:17.988 --> 22:19.642
It's your little one.

22:19.686 --> 22:24.560
If he gets on that school bus
with all this snow,

22:24.604 --> 22:27.433
it's gonna crash.

22:27.476 --> 22:32.046
You need to get home now.

22:32.089 --> 22:35.223
[engine turns over]
[chuckles evilly]

22:35.266 --> 22:37.094
♪

22:37.138 --> 22:39.183
[engine revs]

22:41.011 --> 22:47.714
♪

22:47.757 --> 22:49.977
- [sighs]

23:13.130 --> 23:15.481
- He told me
he was innocent...

23:15.524 --> 23:17.178
that he didn't hurt
that girl.

23:17.221 --> 23:19.528
I believed him.

23:19.572 --> 23:21.225
I feel so stupid.

23:21.269 --> 23:22.575
- Just help us
find him, Deborah,

23:22.618 --> 23:24.011
so he can't do this
to anybody else.

23:24.054 --> 23:25.534
- What was your plan?

23:25.578 --> 23:27.623
You couldn't stay
in that apartment forever.

23:27.667 --> 23:30.974
- I was gonna
trade in my car...

23:31.018 --> 23:34.021
get us some new clothes,
hair dye.

23:34.064 --> 23:36.110
He was gonna talk
to his friend Ed.

23:36.153 --> 23:38.112
Ed was gonna tell him
what to do next.

23:38.155 --> 23:39.200
- Ed Roven?

23:39.243 --> 23:41.463
- He didn't give me
a last name.

23:41.507 --> 23:44.597
But I heard them talking
this morning in the other room.

23:44.640 --> 23:48.601
That was right before
Mark attacked me.

23:48.644 --> 23:51.386
I thought the four of us
were leaving together,

23:51.430 --> 23:55.172
but then Mark said,
"Plans change, Cottontail."

23:55.216 --> 23:57.000
- Detectives, we need
to get her to a hospital.

23:57.044 --> 23:58.262
- Hang on, we're almost done.

23:58.306 --> 23:59.742
- What do you mean
the four of you?

23:59.786 --> 24:03.137
- Mark and me
and Ed and Ed's girlfriend.

24:03.180 --> 24:04.791
- Who's Ed's girlfriend?

24:04.834 --> 24:07.489
- I never met her...
[sniffles]

24:07.533 --> 24:09.752
But Mark said I'd like her.

24:09.796 --> 24:12.712
She was special, he said.

24:12.755 --> 24:14.670
She knows things.

24:14.714 --> 24:18.195
♪

24:18.239 --> 24:20.328
- He's going after Cassie.

24:20.371 --> 24:23.374
[cell phone vibrating]

24:26.160 --> 24:28.510
- Hey, Cassie.
- [shrieks]

24:28.554 --> 24:30.512
[whimpering]

24:30.556 --> 24:33.384
[suspenseful music]

24:33.428 --> 24:35.517
♪

24:35.561 --> 24:37.737
You bitch.

24:37.780 --> 24:43.046
♪

24:43.090 --> 24:45.527
Come on, Cottontail,
I just want to play.

24:45.571 --> 24:48.138
- [whimpering]

24:48.182 --> 24:51.533
[panting]

24:51.577 --> 24:54.536
[screams, gasping]

24:54.580 --> 24:56.495
[wails, chokes]

24:56.538 --> 24:59.715
♪

24:59.759 --> 25:02.675
- [chuckles]

25:02.718 --> 25:07.375
♪

25:07.418 --> 25:08.637
[vase shatters]

25:08.681 --> 25:10.509
[electricity crackling]

25:10.552 --> 25:12.423
- [grunting]

25:12.467 --> 25:14.077
♪

25:14.121 --> 25:15.470
[screams]

25:15.514 --> 25:17.385
[body thuds]

25:17.428 --> 25:20.388
- [breathing heavily]

25:20.431 --> 25:25.262
♪

25:25.306 --> 25:26.829
[shudders]

25:26.873 --> 25:29.876
[eerie whooshing]

25:29.919 --> 25:31.486
♪

25:31.530 --> 25:33.836
- This ain't over,
Cassie girl.

25:33.880 --> 25:36.404
I'm coming for you...

25:36.447 --> 25:38.537
and everyone you love.

25:38.580 --> 25:42.149
♪

25:45.413 --> 25:45.761
.

25:45.805 --> 25:47.197
[indistinct chatter]

25:47.241 --> 25:48.372
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

25:48.416 --> 25:50.810
- Sure thing.
- Here, take this.

25:50.853 --> 25:52.855
- Really, you guys,
stop fussing.

25:52.899 --> 25:54.378
- For inflammation.
Put it on it.

25:54.422 --> 25:56.772
- I'm okay.
- Yeah, define okay.

25:56.816 --> 25:58.121
There's a big difference
between fighting

25:58.165 --> 26:00.123
non-corporeal monsters
and real live ones.

26:00.167 --> 26:01.951
- Nothing's broken, I swear.

26:01.995 --> 26:04.780
- All the same, maybe we should
postpone the surgery.

26:04.824 --> 26:07.217
- It's only
a few hours away.

26:08.305 --> 26:10.090
- W-we're all stressed out.

26:10.133 --> 26:11.744
- Babe, you heard
what the doctor said.

26:11.787 --> 26:14.137
We don't have a choice.

26:14.181 --> 26:16.531
- Why?
What did the doctor say?

26:16.575 --> 26:20.361
[somber music]

26:20.404 --> 26:23.146
- The tumor hasn't been
shrinking as fast as we'd like.

26:23.190 --> 26:24.757
♪

26:24.800 --> 26:27.150
Steroids aren't doing the job.

26:27.194 --> 26:28.761
♪

26:28.804 --> 26:30.197
- And you didn't tell me?

26:30.240 --> 26:32.025
- Because surgery
will fix the problem.

26:32.068 --> 26:33.896
The woman that they're
flying in to do the procedure,

26:33.940 --> 26:36.377
Dr. Ashcroft, she's one
of the best in the world.

26:36.420 --> 26:37.857
But if we don't do it now,

26:37.900 --> 26:39.336
she won't be available again
for months.

26:39.380 --> 26:40.947
- And that's months
spent waiting,

26:40.990 --> 26:42.209
the tumor still growing.

26:42.252 --> 26:45.473
It's--it's just what it is.

26:45.516 --> 26:49.216
♪

26:49.259 --> 26:51.218
- Well, I don't know
the answer.

26:51.261 --> 26:53.263
- Then we have to have faith...

26:53.307 --> 26:55.222
that everything will be okay.

26:55.265 --> 26:58.965
♪

26:59.008 --> 27:01.097
Sweetie...

27:01.141 --> 27:02.446
You're wearing
Mom's necklace.

27:02.490 --> 27:04.231
- Yeah.

27:04.274 --> 27:06.363
Something told me to put it on.

27:06.407 --> 27:09.062
I guess I was hoping
it would bring me luck...

27:09.105 --> 27:10.454
a little extra strength.

27:10.498 --> 27:12.326
- Maybe she was there
with you

27:12.369 --> 27:14.502
when you were
fighting off Waterman.

27:14.545 --> 27:16.896
- Maybe.

27:16.939 --> 27:20.247
If so, then I hope
she stays around...

27:20.290 --> 27:22.815
sticks with you
during your procedure.

27:22.858 --> 27:24.947
♪

27:24.991 --> 27:27.341
- So we're doing this.
- [inhales deeply]

27:27.384 --> 27:29.604
♪

27:29.648 --> 27:31.867
Yeah, we're doing this.

27:31.911 --> 27:35.610
♪

27:35.654 --> 27:38.613
[indistinct chatter]

27:38.657 --> 27:40.920
♪

27:40.963 --> 27:44.010
[woman speaking indistinctly
over PA]

27:44.053 --> 27:46.447
- [inhales deeply]
This is it, kids.

27:46.490 --> 27:47.970
♪

27:48.014 --> 27:49.493
I'll see you
in about ten hours.

27:49.537 --> 27:52.018
- We'll be here every second.

27:52.061 --> 27:53.933
[door buzzes]
- Wait.

27:53.976 --> 27:56.326
♪

27:56.370 --> 27:58.502
[no audible dialogue]

27:58.546 --> 28:05.553
♪

28:10.036 --> 28:13.474
- I love you.
- I love you.

28:13.517 --> 28:15.171
- I love you, Brian.

28:15.215 --> 28:18.174
♪

28:18.218 --> 28:20.176
[door buzzes]

28:20.220 --> 28:24.180
♪

28:24.224 --> 28:26.574
[door closes]

28:26.617 --> 28:29.446
[exhales sharply]
- [sighs shakily]

28:29.490 --> 28:32.319
[distant sirens wailing,
indistinct chatter]

28:32.362 --> 28:34.495
[woman speaking indistinctly
over PA]

28:34.538 --> 28:35.975
- Hey.

28:36.018 --> 28:38.325
I hope it's okay
I came to wait with you.

28:38.368 --> 28:40.109
- Yeah.
Please, yeah.

28:40.153 --> 28:41.589
Distract us.

28:41.632 --> 28:43.373
- It's been hours.
No word.

28:43.417 --> 28:46.028
They were supposed to be
finished by now, weren't they?

28:46.072 --> 28:47.638
- It's a complicated procedure.

28:47.682 --> 28:50.598
- Well, I brought you guys...

28:50.641 --> 28:51.947
some food.

28:51.991 --> 28:53.557
- Appreciate it.
Thank you.

28:53.601 --> 28:56.343
- Thank you. I'm just gonna go
for a walk around the hall.

28:56.386 --> 28:58.127
I'll be right back.

28:58.171 --> 29:00.129
- We'll be here.

29:00.173 --> 29:02.523
[man speaking indistinctly
over PA]

29:02.566 --> 29:06.266
- [sighs]

29:06.309 --> 29:09.922
[woman speaking indistinctly
over PA]

29:21.934 --> 29:25.459
[breathes deeply]

29:34.729 --> 29:37.906
[breathes deeply]

29:42.606 --> 29:45.044
[breathing shakily]

29:45.087 --> 29:47.698
[claps hands]

29:47.742 --> 29:51.702
Whoever or whatever you are...

29:51.746 --> 29:54.314
up there...

29:54.357 --> 29:56.403
[sighs]

29:56.446 --> 30:00.711
I feel like I've been sending
you prayers my whole life.

30:00.755 --> 30:02.583
Please make it stop,

30:02.626 --> 30:06.979
so I don't have to keep seeing
these awful things.

30:08.763 --> 30:12.158
Please make my mom
quit drinking.

30:12.201 --> 30:14.334
Please don't let my mom die.

30:17.337 --> 30:19.295
Maybe you're sick of me
asking for things

30:19.339 --> 30:21.341
you'll never make happen.

30:23.560 --> 30:25.780
I get that.

30:25.824 --> 30:28.174
But here's the deal...

30:30.567 --> 30:33.657
If you want to keep sending me
this horrible stuff

30:33.701 --> 30:36.486
and you want me to keep
doing something about it,

30:36.530 --> 30:39.707
then you leave Brian alone.

30:41.491 --> 30:44.407
You let him stay right here
with Tom and me.

30:44.451 --> 30:47.193
[dramatic music]

30:47.236 --> 30:50.065
If you don't...

30:50.109 --> 30:52.807
if you don't do that--
if you take him...

30:52.851 --> 30:54.983
♪

30:55.027 --> 30:57.768
[inhales sharply]

30:57.812 --> 31:00.815
Then I won't give you
what you want either.

31:00.859 --> 31:02.991
♪

31:03.035 --> 31:05.385
I'll just walk away.

31:05.428 --> 31:08.692
You can rain down visions
on my head,

31:08.736 --> 31:12.044
and I will bat them away
just as fast.

31:12.087 --> 31:14.002
I don't care if I go mad.

31:14.046 --> 31:16.265
[scoffs]

31:16.309 --> 31:18.789
I don't care if I die.

31:18.833 --> 31:21.227
♪

31:21.270 --> 31:25.057
So think long and hard
about this.

31:25.100 --> 31:26.580
♪

31:26.623 --> 31:29.365
Think about
what you'll be losing...

31:29.409 --> 31:34.109
♪

31:34.153 --> 31:36.372
If you even care.

31:36.416 --> 31:38.374
[eerie whooshing]

31:38.418 --> 31:41.377
- [clapping hands slowly]

31:41.421 --> 31:45.425
♪

31:45.468 --> 31:47.731
That was beautiful,
Cottontail.

31:47.775 --> 31:53.041
♪

31:56.392 --> 31:56.827
.

31:56.871 --> 31:59.265
[dramatic music]

31:59.308 --> 32:02.355
- Of course you're here.

32:02.398 --> 32:06.011
You're never more happy,
are you, Ed...

32:06.054 --> 32:08.100
than when I am scared
and alone.

32:08.143 --> 32:11.799
- Now, that's harsh,
Cassie girl.

32:11.842 --> 32:15.977
You know as well as I do it
didn't have to end like this.

32:16.021 --> 32:17.805
We make a good team,
you and me.

32:17.848 --> 32:19.850
- We were never a team.

32:19.894 --> 32:22.375
- Maybe we are better off
as enemies.

32:22.418 --> 32:24.464
♪

32:24.507 --> 32:26.683
At least we know
where we stand.

32:26.727 --> 32:29.860
- Can you tell me something?
Was any of it true?

32:29.904 --> 32:32.124
That whole "doing good deeds

32:32.167 --> 32:34.169
to buy your way
into Heaven" bit--

32:34.213 --> 32:37.999
did you believe any of it?

32:38.043 --> 32:41.307
- There was a moment there
when it was true.

32:41.350 --> 32:44.875
But I thought to myself, "Well,
it's never too late to change."

32:44.919 --> 32:46.703
- But then Millie Pierce
punched a hole

32:46.747 --> 32:48.357
through the inbetween
and showed us both

32:48.401 --> 32:51.360
who you really are
and what you'll always be--

32:51.404 --> 32:53.058
a killer.

32:53.101 --> 32:55.016
- And bless her for that.

32:55.060 --> 32:57.366
[chuckles]

32:57.410 --> 32:59.847
40 years on Earth,

32:59.890 --> 33:03.720
20 years-plus in this limbo,

33:03.764 --> 33:08.334
trying and failing
to deny my true nature.

33:08.377 --> 33:10.336
But that's all over now.

33:10.379 --> 33:12.338
How long do you think
it'll take me

33:12.381 --> 33:15.384
to create
another Waterman?

33:15.428 --> 33:18.431
A month?
A year?

33:18.474 --> 33:20.389
Sooner or later,
someone's gonna come

33:20.433 --> 33:24.045
to snuff out your life
and deliver your spirit to me.

33:24.089 --> 33:25.525
♪

33:25.568 --> 33:27.962
And there'll be nothing left
of the girl you are now

33:28.006 --> 33:30.051
once he's done.

33:30.095 --> 33:33.794
Just black holes where them
pretty green eyes used to be.

33:33.837 --> 33:35.143
♪

33:35.187 --> 33:38.364
So you just keep looking
over your shoulder...

33:38.407 --> 33:42.063
because I got all the time
in the world.

33:42.107 --> 33:43.847
- That is where you are wrong.

33:43.891 --> 33:46.372
Your time is up, Ed.

33:46.415 --> 33:50.071
I'm sending you down
to the dark place.

33:50.115 --> 33:52.073
Oh..

33:52.117 --> 33:55.207
just the thought of it,
it--it scares you, doesn't it?

33:55.250 --> 33:56.817
♪

33:56.860 --> 33:59.211
Because you know
that is where you should be.

33:59.254 --> 34:02.866
You've been hiding
in the inbetween for years,

34:02.910 --> 34:06.261
making these fake attempts
at atonement,

34:06.305 --> 34:08.220
all the while hoping
that nobody notices

34:08.263 --> 34:10.222
that little old Ed Roven--

34:10.265 --> 34:12.789
he's not where he belongs.

34:12.833 --> 34:14.878
♪

34:14.922 --> 34:16.924
You'd better get
your affairs in order.

34:16.967 --> 34:19.274
- You don't have
nearly that kind of power.

34:19.318 --> 34:21.015
[eerie whooshing]

34:21.059 --> 34:22.843
- I wouldn't be too sure
about that.

34:22.886 --> 34:25.237
- [chuckles]

34:25.280 --> 34:27.500
- Well, well...

34:27.543 --> 34:29.502
who's this niblet?

34:29.545 --> 34:31.156
- I'm Cassie's friend.

34:31.199 --> 34:34.159
- [laughing]

34:34.202 --> 34:35.377
♪

34:35.421 --> 34:37.249
Can you do any tricks?

34:37.292 --> 34:39.425
[air whooshes]
[grunts]

34:39.468 --> 34:43.037
[laughs]
That's cute.

34:43.081 --> 34:45.300
But it's gonna take
more than one little girl

34:45.344 --> 34:46.954
to get rid of me.

34:46.997 --> 34:49.130
- Which is why
she brought backup.

34:49.174 --> 34:50.958
[eerie whooshing]

34:51.001 --> 34:52.351
- Hi, Ed.

34:52.394 --> 34:56.529
♪

34:56.572 --> 34:58.966
- Millie.

34:59.009 --> 35:00.881
What are you doing here, baby?

35:00.924 --> 35:02.448
- She's here for you.

35:02.491 --> 35:04.972
- What are you talking about?
- Remember what you told me?

35:05.015 --> 35:07.148
Remember?

35:07.192 --> 35:10.456
Best to let the dead deal
with their own.

35:10.499 --> 35:17.027
♪

35:17.071 --> 35:20.335
They're all here, Ed...

35:20.379 --> 35:22.294
your victims.

35:22.337 --> 35:25.993
♪

35:26.036 --> 35:28.300
You took the lives
of these women.

35:28.343 --> 35:31.477
Now they have come
for your soul.

35:31.520 --> 35:33.435
- Hang on.

35:33.479 --> 35:35.307
Hang on!

35:35.350 --> 35:38.484
[grunting, screaming]

35:38.527 --> 35:45.534
♪

35:52.628 --> 35:55.196
- [breathes deeply]

35:55.240 --> 35:57.546
Thank you.

35:57.590 --> 36:00.201
I can't believe you found
the others so fast.

36:00.245 --> 36:02.899
After you told me how big
the inbetween was,

36:02.943 --> 36:04.901
I was...

36:04.945 --> 36:08.035
managing my expectations.

36:08.078 --> 36:09.645
- It was even harder
than I thought.

36:09.689 --> 36:12.257
I couldn't find Millie
or anyone.

36:12.300 --> 36:14.215
But then I got some help.

36:14.259 --> 36:15.564
- From who?

36:15.608 --> 36:17.262
- Just this nice lady.

36:17.305 --> 36:19.960
She said her name was Clare.

36:22.267 --> 36:24.530
- That's my mother's name.

36:24.573 --> 36:27.097
Was she wearing a lilac coat?

36:27.141 --> 36:29.187
Kind of like--like this color.

36:29.230 --> 36:31.058
- And a white cap.

36:31.101 --> 36:34.496
[soft music]

36:34.540 --> 36:37.630
- She didn't give you
a message for me.

36:37.673 --> 36:39.153
- No.

36:39.197 --> 36:41.242
Sorry.

36:41.286 --> 36:43.026
But without her,

36:43.070 --> 36:45.551
I don't think
I could have done it, Cassie.

36:45.594 --> 36:47.727
She really helped.

36:47.770 --> 36:50.556
♪

36:50.599 --> 36:52.993
- I'm glad you got to meet her.

36:53.036 --> 36:56.431
♪

36:56.475 --> 36:59.391
If you see her again,
tell her I said...

36:59.434 --> 37:02.350
not to be a stranger.

37:02.394 --> 37:05.005
- Okay, I will.

37:05.048 --> 37:07.703
♪

37:07.747 --> 37:09.488
Bye, Cassie.

37:09.531 --> 37:12.012
♪

37:12.055 --> 37:14.057
- Good-bye, Abigail.

37:14.101 --> 37:21.108
♪

37:23.676 --> 37:25.286
[gasps]

37:25.330 --> 37:27.984
Oh, no, no, no, no,
please.

37:28.028 --> 37:30.596
- Dr. Ashcroft, please come
to third-floor recovery.

37:30.639 --> 37:32.467
Code blue.
- No.

37:32.511 --> 37:35.688
- Dr. Ashcroft to third-floor
recovery--code blue.

37:35.731 --> 37:37.603
- The doctor's the best
in her field.

37:37.646 --> 37:39.126
They're doing everything
they can.

37:39.169 --> 37:40.475
- What happened?
What happened?

37:40.519 --> 37:44.044
- They--they're not sure.
He was fine, and then...

37:44.087 --> 37:46.307
he--uh, he started to crash.
[clears throat]

37:46.351 --> 37:48.135
- The doctor's in with him now.

37:48.178 --> 37:50.224
- Wait here.
I'll find out what's going on.

37:50.268 --> 37:52.661
- Thank you.
- [sighs]

37:52.705 --> 37:55.316
[somber music]

37:55.360 --> 37:58.319
- [crying softly]

37:58.363 --> 38:04.194
♪

38:04.238 --> 38:06.458
[Asante sighs]

38:06.501 --> 38:08.634
- We should have
postponed the surgery.

38:08.677 --> 38:10.462
I should have said something.

38:10.505 --> 38:12.768
I had the answer.
I just--

38:12.812 --> 38:14.770
I was afraid to say so.

38:14.814 --> 38:18.121
- What are you talking about?

38:18.165 --> 38:20.689
- Cassie saw Brian...

38:20.733 --> 38:23.649
the same way she saw Sally
before Sally died.

38:23.692 --> 38:25.564
♪

38:25.607 --> 38:28.131
- I am so sorry.

38:28.175 --> 38:33.267
♪

38:33.311 --> 38:36.488
- Listen, you, none of this
is your fault, okay?

38:36.531 --> 38:38.490
None of it.

38:38.533 --> 38:40.492
♪

38:40.535 --> 38:43.625
Brian told you
what the doctor said.

38:43.669 --> 38:46.062
We had to do
the surgery today, okay?

38:46.106 --> 38:48.369
And even if you had told us...

38:48.413 --> 38:51.198
♪

38:51.241 --> 38:53.200
What you saw...

38:53.243 --> 38:55.289
we still would have done it.

38:55.333 --> 38:57.291
[sighs]

38:57.335 --> 38:59.380
- How can you be sure?

38:59.424 --> 39:02.252
- 'Cause we talked about it.

39:02.296 --> 39:03.471
These are
conversations you have

39:03.515 --> 39:06.692
when your child is gifted.

39:06.735 --> 39:09.129
- Mr. Hackett?
- Dr. Ashcroft.

39:09.172 --> 39:11.131
- Sorry you had to wait
so long for news,

39:11.174 --> 39:12.480
but I just wanted
to be positive

39:12.524 --> 39:13.829
he was out of the woods.

39:13.873 --> 39:16.092
Now, his heart did stop
for a moment,

39:16.136 --> 39:17.659
but we were able
to resuscitate him.

39:17.703 --> 39:20.532
- You're saying he was dead?
- For about 15 seconds, yes.

39:20.575 --> 39:22.838
- But he's all right?
- He's stabilized.

39:22.882 --> 39:24.666
He's awake and talking.

39:24.710 --> 39:27.321
I'd say the procedure
was a complete success.

39:27.365 --> 39:30.411
[both laugh, sigh]

39:30.455 --> 39:32.413
- If you just
give him a minute,

39:32.457 --> 39:33.893
you can go in and see him.

39:33.936 --> 39:35.460
- Thank you.
- Come here, you.

39:35.503 --> 39:38.419
- [laughing]
- That's great news, man.

39:38.463 --> 39:40.421
- Yeah.
- [laughs]

39:40.465 --> 39:42.292
- [sniffles]

39:42.336 --> 39:44.251
- Come here.

39:44.294 --> 39:46.166
Thank you, Damien.
- No worries.

39:46.209 --> 39:49.212
I'm just--I'm just glad
it's a happy ending.

39:49.256 --> 39:52.259
- I'm so sorry it wasn't
a happy ending...

39:52.302 --> 39:53.739
for everyone.

39:53.782 --> 39:57.482
- I was with Sally
when she passed.

39:57.525 --> 40:00.789
Every day I'm grateful for that
last message you brought me.

40:00.833 --> 40:02.400
[sighs]

40:02.443 --> 40:04.619
But the universe
keeps turning, right?

40:04.663 --> 40:06.229
- Yeah.
- All right.

40:06.273 --> 40:07.927
Let's hope
for better days ahead.

40:07.970 --> 40:10.930
[uplifting music]

40:10.973 --> 40:15.761
♪

40:15.804 --> 40:18.764
[woman speaking indistinctly
over PA]

40:18.807 --> 40:19.939
- I know it sounds crazy,

40:19.982 --> 40:21.157
but I just want
to get back to work.

40:21.201 --> 40:23.682
- Not so fast.
You need to rest up.

40:23.725 --> 40:25.553
- I've been doing nothing
but resting for months now.

40:25.597 --> 40:28.861
- At least let us take care of
you for another week or two.

40:28.904 --> 40:31.733
The chance to be waited on
hand and foot

40:31.777 --> 40:33.431
might not come again.

40:33.474 --> 40:36.303
- [laughs]
Seriously, Brian.

40:36.346 --> 40:39.567
You've got to take it easy...
at least for a few weeks.

40:39.611 --> 40:40.960
- Maybe when I feel up to it,

40:41.003 --> 40:43.223
we can drive out to that
little place in La Conner.

40:43.266 --> 40:45.965
- Mm, long weekend
the two of us, right?

40:46.008 --> 40:48.968
[sinister music]

40:49.011 --> 40:51.492
- You must be Cassie.

40:51.536 --> 40:55.278
You look just like your mother.

40:55.322 --> 40:57.498
♪

40:57.542 --> 41:01.284
- Everything all right,
sweetheart?

41:01.328 --> 41:03.504
- Yes, everything's fine.

41:03.548 --> 41:06.942
♪

41:06.986 --> 41:09.815
Everything's just fine.

41:09.858 --> 41:14.254
♪
